rm(list= ls())

medal <- read.csv (file = "Medals.csv")
medal
population <- read.csv (file = "population_by_country_2020_new.csv")
population
GDP <- read.csv (file = "GDP_annual_growth.csv")
GDP
ISO3V10 <- read.csv (file = "ISO3V10.csv")
ISO3V10
medalperpopulation = left_join(medal, population, 
                             by = c("Team" = "Country"))

medal_population.df <- medalperpopulation %>% 
  mutate(medal_population = Total/Population)

medalperGDP = left_join(medalperpopulation, GDP, 
                             by = c("Team" = "Country.Name"))
medalperGDP
#chars <- sapply(medalperGDP, is.character)
inte <- sapply(medalperGDP, is.integer)

medalperGDP[ , inte] <- as.data.frame(apply(medalperGDP[ , inte], 2, as.numeric))

medal_GDP.df <- medalperGDP %>% 
  mutate(GDP = as.numeric(GDP)) %>% 
  mutate(medal_GDP = Total/GDP)
## Warning in mask$eval_all_mutate(quo): NAs introduced by coercion
merge1 <- full_join(medal_population.df, medal_GDP.df)
## Joining, by = c("Rank", "Team", "Gold", "Silver", "Bronze", "Total", "Rank.by.Total", "Population", "Yearly.Change", "Net.Change", "Density..P.Km..", "Land.Area..Km..", "Migrants..net.", "Fert..Rate", "Med..Age", "Urban.Pop..", "World.Share")
medal_population_top10.df = merge1 %>%
  filter(Total >= 30 )

medal_population.df %>% arrange(desc(medal_population))
medal_population_new.df = merge1 %>%
  filter(medal_population >= 2.05e-06 )




medal_GDP.df %>% arrange(desc(medal_GDP))
medal_GDP_new.df = merge1 %>%
  filter( medal_GDP <= 1.00e-09 ) %>% 
  filter(medal_GDP >= 1.47e-10 )
  

merge2 <- full_join(medal_GDP_new.df, medal_population_new.df)
## Joining, by = c("Rank", "Team", "Gold", "Silver", "Bronze", "Total", "Rank.by.Total", "Population", "Yearly.Change", "Net.Change", "Density..P.Km..", "Land.Area..Km..", "Migrants..net.", "Fert..Rate", "Med..Age", "Urban.Pop..", "World.Share", "medal_population", "GDP", "X", "medal_GDP")
merge3 <- full_join(merge2, medal_population_top10.df)
## Joining, by = c("Rank", "Team", "Gold", "Silver", "Bronze", "Total", "Rank.by.Total", "Population", "Yearly.Change", "Net.Change", "Density..P.Km..", "Land.Area..Km..", "Migrants..net.", "Fert..Rate", "Med..Age", "Urban.Pop..", "World.Share", "medal_population", "GDP", "X", "medal_GDP")
#theme_set(theme_bw(base_size=5))

#Medal count with order
 ggplot(data = merge3, aes(x = reorder(Team, Total), y = Total)) +
  geom_col(color = "black", fill="#0072B2", size = 0.5) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size = 10)) +
  coord_flip()+
  scale_fill_viridis_c()+
   labs(title = "2020 tokyo olympics medal count",
       x = "Country", y = "Medal Count",
       caption = "Datasource:Olympics Channel")

tooltip <- merge3 %>%
  mutate(
    tooltip_text = paste0(toupper(Team), "\n", 
                   Total)
  )


graph1 <- ggplot(tooltip, 
                aes(x = reorder(Team, Total), 
                    y = Total,
                   tooltip = tooltip_text, data_id = Team)) +
  geom_col_interactive(color = "black", fill="#0072B2", size = 0.5) + 
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size = 4)) + 
  labs(title = "2020 tokyo olympics medal count",
      caption = "Datasource:Olympics Channel") +
   ylab("") +
   xlab("") +
  coord_flip()

girafe(ggobj = graph1, width_svg = 4.5, height_svg = 2.5)
#Medal count per capita
ggplot(data = merge3, aes(x = reorder(Team, medal_population), y = medal_population)) +
  geom_col(color = "black", fill="#0072B2", size = 0.5) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size = 10)) +
  coord_flip()+
  scale_fill_viridis_c()+
   labs(title = "2020 tokyo olympics medal per capita",
       x = "Country", y = "Medal Count per capita",
       caption = "Datasource:Olympics Channel")

 tooltip2 <- merge3 %>%
  mutate(
    tooltip_text = paste0(toupper(Team), "\n", 
                   medal_population)
  )

graph2 <- ggplot(tooltip2, 
                aes(x = reorder(Team,medal_population ), 
                    y = medal_population,
                    tooltip = tooltip_text, data_id = Team)) +
  geom_col_interactive(color = "black", fill="#0072B2", size = 0.5) + 
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size = 4)) + 
  labs(title = "2020 tokyo olympics medal count per capita",
      caption = "Datasource:Olympics Channel" ) +
   scale_fill_viridis_c()+
   ylab("") +
   xlab("") +
  coord_flip()

girafe(ggobj = graph2, width_svg = 4.5, height_svg = 2.5)
girafe(code = print(graph1 + graph2),  width_svg = 8, height_svg = 4) %>% 
  girafe_options(opts_hover(css = "fill:cyan;"))
#Medal count per GDP
